<p>I'm trying to set the initial value of a Choice Field dynamically, in the view. But it doesn't work, not sure what is wrong:</p>  <p>views.py</p>  <pre><code>... form = FormEditGroup(initial={             'choices_a': group.get_a(),             'choices_i': group.get_i(),             }) </code></pre>  <p><code>get_a()</code> is a model method that returns "open" or "closed", <code>get_i()</code> returns "admins" or "all". </p>  <p>forms.py</p>  <pre><code>class FormEditGroup(forms.Form):     choices_a = (("closed", "Closed"), ("open", "Open"))     choices_i = (("all", "All"), ("admins", "Admins"))      a = forms.ChoiceField(... choices=choices_a),     i = forms.ChoiceField(... choices=choices_i), </code></pre>  <p>It is not setting the initial value to what <code>get_a()</code> or <code>get_i()</code> return.</p>